:javascript
  // Inject UI fragments from Rails so JS modules stay DRY without hardcoding HTML.
  // This specifically allows DataTables rendering (e.g., `dt_yes_no_pill_renderer` in `cafe_datatable.js`) 
  // to inherit the exact same HTML and Bootstrap CSS classes generated by the Rails backend 
  // (e.g., `ApplicationHelper#format_key_pair_value`), keeping the design system unified.
  //
  // Note: We use `window.CafeUI` distinctly instead of appending to the existing `cafe` variable
  // because `cafe` is imported across the frontend as an immutable ES module (`import * as cafe`),
  // and `application.js` globally clobbers `window.cafe` on load, which would erase these injections.
  window.CafeUI = {
    badges: {
      yes: "#{j format_key_pair_value(true, :yes_no)}",
      no: "#{j format_key_pair_value(false, :yes_no)}"
    }
  }
